title: Sneed scores OT winner, Golden Eagles squeeze past Creekside
text:
Sneed scores OT winner, Golden Eagles squeeze past Creekside 
Sat, Oct 17, 2015 @ 12:27 am 
FLEMING ISLAND 23 
CREEKSIDE (OT) 17 
Fleming senior RB Trey Sneed rushed for 161 yards and the decisive TD in overtime as the Golden Eagles beat Creekside 23-17 in a District 3-7A contest. Fleming (1-2, 4-3) rallied from a 17-7 deficit in the third quarter. Creekside (0-2, 0-7) lost its 10th consecutive contest and had two chances late to win, but missed two long field goals within the last six minutes of the game. ... Sneed’s 10-yard run on the first play of overtime gave Fleming the 23-17 lead, but left-footed place-kicker Hakeem Reid — who kicked a 45-yard field goal early in the fourth quarter to tie the score at 17-17 — bounced his extra point off the left upright to give Creekside a chance to win. However, Creekside moved backward on its overtime possession from the 10-yard line as a fourth-down pass from the 22 was intercepted to end the game. Senior RB Blake Morgan rushed for 167 yards and a TD for Creekside.
